## Dev server and mobile testing

```bash
npm run dev          # desktop — http://localhost:3000
npm run dev:https    # mobile — https://localhost:3000 + https://<LAN-IP>:3000
```

Service workers only register on HTTPS or `localhost`. Always use `dev:https` when testing offline mode or SW behaviour on a real device.

`dev:https` is not included by default. Add it once per project (requires [mkcert](https://github.com/FiloSottile/mkcert)):

```bash
npx socle cert
```

This prompts for shared (`~/.socle-certs/`, reused across projects) or project-specific certs, runs `mkcert`, and adds the `dev:https` script to `package.json`. The Android CA install walkthrough runs automatically if you enter a LAN IP.

**Testing offline:**
1. Start `npm run dev:https`
2. Visit the HTTPS URL on the device — wait a few seconds for the SW to install and pre-cache all assets
3. Kill the server (`pkill -f "serve dist"`)
4. Reload on the device — the app should load fully from cache

Cert files (`*.pem`, `*.key`, `*.crt`) are gitignored — never commit them.

